I love this answer (borrowed from a friend) PSA: There is nothing genetically inferior about Black people that is making them more susceptible to this virus, and to believe otherwise is racist. The reason Black people are disproportionately infected and dying from Coronavirus is systemic and structural racism and I sincerely wish that the media would just use those words to describe the issue.1) Black Americans are less likely to be tested for the virus than their white counterparts2) Black Americans are less likely to be treated for the virus than their white counterparts3) Black Americans are more likely to be "essential workers" and have to keep going into work, meaning disproportionate exposure to the virus 4) Black Americans are more likely to come from socioeconomic backgrounds where they are forced to take public transportation, meaning disproportionate exposure to the virus5) Black Americans are less likely to have access to quality healthcare, period. 6) When Black Americans have access to even the best healthcare, study after study shows their concerns are taken less seriously than the concerns of their white counterparts. 7) Many of the underlying conditions that Black Americans suffer from which make them more likely to die from the virus are due to deeper, structural inequities (such as living in food deserts, lacking access or resources to necessary preventative care, etc). I am more saddened than my own 2020 graduate not to be able to attend the long-awaited graduation ceremony at Swarthmore in the beautiful Pennsylvania arboretum! The culmination of all those days and nights I spent with her filling out admissions forms and financial aid forms and more forms and papers - I needed to see that come down to that moment where we could all come together to celebrate all of our hard work. Now it will be spent at home watching some sort of graduation ceremony on our TV, just many faces of the graduates popping by, one after the other, likely some music and words from the President. But as with all things we need to focus above and beyond on the things that really matter. To set our sights on greater things. To create our own special, magical moments. I have been inspired. US20200097951 - CRYPTOCURRENCY SYSTEM USING BODY ACTIVITY DATA

Abstract Human body activity associated with a task provided to a user may be used in a mining process of a cryptocurrency system. A server may provide a task to a device of a user which is communicatively coupled to the server. A sensor communicatively coupled to or comprised in the device of the user may sense body activity of the user. Body activity data may be generated based on the sensed body activity of the user. The cryptocurrency system communicatively coupled to the device of the user may verify if the body activity data satisfies one or more conditions set by the cryptocurrency system, and award cryptocurrency to the user whose body activity data is verified.Also published as WO/2020/060606

We as so-called Africa Americans have endured this systemic injustice for decades. We need leaders not music video releases. We need viable education for our children not stimulus checks. Im a paralegal and im working on my husbands case because he cant get legal representation.  The Gardena police interrogated him while he was medicated by the hospital and gave him 40 years to life for a DUI. Nobody died. But they gave him life. Say his name Johnnie Echols....his life matters. I live in the Nickerson Gardens projects in Cali and we need viable education for our children. I was married with my first child at 18, my second child at age 21, thrown from a car at 22, divorced by 23 and remarried at 25, completed my BS in Psychology, MS in Counseling Psychology and while at the same graduate school entered into a Ph.d of Psychology program and made all the way to comps to be told I did not write my comps exam as expected. I had many years of writing at that school and never failed a paper but when I shared I was having sickness they took advantage of the moment and would ask what my race was during conversation. I have $189,000 student loan debt, unable to get a home for my family size of 7 now because of student loan debt and income to debt ratio, someone keeps putting negative things on my credit, and I dound out the programs completed does not meet standards for licensure in my major field in their state nor mines and has been limited to become a licensed clinical addiction specialist associate. Now due to covid I am unable to keep a supervisor. I have worked three jobs as a Behavioral Health Specialist, Adjunct Professor of Psychology, and Consultant for 11 to 14 years and wasn't afforded the ability to do anything when I had to got out on disability and I have seen many whites given so much flexibility. I turned 40 this year in hopes to have my dream home, but that didn't happen. Income has went down to poverty-stricken and I have been sick still trying. No one to help. Sometimes I see why my patients feel that dying is the best solution. We are all human but treat each other worse than we would animals. So hurt by the mirage of social injustice, limited resources, and racial discrimination. Many of my clients could have good lives with resources. Resources, love, and support is the true therapy and solution to our world crisis, but never addressed due to the feeling of giving a handout. Isn't donations handouts? Handouts that give temporary  solutions to problems people feel. Blacks are so deprived. We don't be positive and support each other because there is so much hurt and bitterness. Lives are loss but there are so many here to be helped and saved from more than death.
